<div class="help">
  <p><%= link_to 'Textile', 'http://hobix.com/textile/quick.html' %> is supported. You can also use
  raw HTML.</p>

  <p>Links to other wiki pages:
  <code>[[wiki-page-id]]</code> or
  <code>[[Wiki page title]]</code> or
  <code>"Text of link":[[wiki-page-id]]</code> or
  <code>"Text of link":[[Wiki page title]]</code>.</p>

  <p>Format source code samples like this:</p>

  <div class="usercontent">
    <pre><code class="html">
    &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="javascript"&gt;
      function helloWorld() {
        alert("Hello world");
      }
    &lt;/code&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
    </code></pre>
  </div>

  <p>Specify programming language the sample is in with <code>class="language"</code> on
  <code>code</code> element.</p>
</div>
